Package openconnector

Interface Summary
Connector A Connector serves as a common interface for low-level communication to a resource.
ConnectorStateChangeListener The ConnectorStateChangeListener bridges the gap between OpenConnectorAdapter and the openconnectors AbstractConector.
Log A Log is a simple logging interface for use by Connector classes.
 

Class Summary
AbstractConnector An abstract implementation of the Connector interfaces that all connectors should extend.
ConnectorConfig A ConnectorConfig contains information about how a connector should connect to a resource, how the connector should behave, and how objects will look on a resource.
Filter A Filter is a representation of criteria that can be used to search for objects.
FilteredIterator An iterator that wraps another iterator and filters such that the returned objects must match the provided filter.
Item A model for a single change request for an object.
JsonBuilder Utility class for rendering JSON.
Partition A Partition is an object that is used by the connector interface to describe slices of data that can be split up during object iteration.
Permission A model for complex entitlements.
Plan A model to represent a set of provisioning requests for a connector.
Request A model to represent a request for a single target object.
Result A model to represent a result from a provisioning request.
Schema A Schema describes the attributes that are supported in a resource object.
Schema.Attribute The definition of a resource object attribute.
SystemOutLog An implementation of the Log interface that sends messages to the system output stream.
 

Enum Summary
Connector.Feature An enumeration of features that a Connector can choose to support.
Filter.Conjunct An enumeration of conjunctions for a composite filter.
Filter.Operator An enumeration of operators for filter criteria.
Item.Operation Operations describe how values should be applied when updating.
Request.Operation Operations specify what is to be done to the object.
Result.Status The set of possible result status codes.
Schema.Type An enumeration of attribute types.
 

Exception Summary
AuthenticationFailedException A connector exception indicating that authentication failed.
ConnectorException A generic exception thrown by connectors when operations fail.
ExpiredPasswordException A connector exception indicating that authentication failed because of an expired password.
ObjectAlreadyExistsException A connector exception indicating that an object with a given name already exists in the resource.
ObjectNotFoundException A connector exception indicating that a requested object cannot be found.
